"priority\\\":{\\\"self\\\":\\\"https://vandanatest01.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/priority/3\\\",\\\"iconUrl\\\":\\\"https://vandanatest01.atlassian.net/images/icons/priorities/medium_new.svg\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Medium\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"3\\\"},\\\"customfield_10001\\\":null,\\\"labels\\\":[],\\\"customfield_10017\\\":null,\\\"environment\\\":null,\\\"customfield_10019\\\":\\\"0|i0004f:\\\",\\\"timeestimate\\\":null,\\\"aggregatetimeoriginalestimate\\\":null,\\\"versions\\\":[],\\\"duedate\\\":null,\\\"progress\\\":{\\\"progress\\\":0,\\\"total\\\":0},\\\"issuelinks\\\":[],\\\"votes\\\":{\\\"self\\\":\\\"https://vandanatest01.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/KAN-12/votes\\\",\\\"votes\\\":0,\\\"hasVoted\\\":false},\\\"comment\\\":{\\\"comments\\\":[],\\\"self\\\":\\\"https://vandanatest01.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/10128/comment\\\",\\\"maxResults\\\":0,\\\"total\\\":0,\\\"startAt\\\":0},\\\"assignee\\\":null,\\\"worklog\\\":{\\\"startAt\\\":0,\\\"maxResults\\\":20,\\\"total\\\":0,\\\"worklogs\\\":[]},\\\"updated\\\":\\\"2026-04-12T01:01:47.202+0530\\\",\\\"status\\\":{\\\"self\\\":\\\"https://vandanatest01.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/10000\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"iconUrl\\\":\\\"https://vandanatest01.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"To Do\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"10000\\\",\\\"statusCategory\\\":{\\\"self\\\":\\\"https://vandanatest01.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/2\\\",\\\"id\\\":2,\\\"key\\\":\\\"new\\\",\\\"colorName\\\":\\\"blue-gray\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"To Do\\\"}}}}]\"],\"options\":{\"api_key\":{\"lc\":1,\"type\":\"secret\",\"id\":[\"GROQ_API_KEY\"]},\"model\":\"openai/gpt-oss-120b\",\"temperature\":0.7},\"response\":{\"response\":{\"generations\":[[{\"text\":\"**Test Plan – App.VWO.com (Jira KAN‑12 – “PRD‑ app.VWO.com”)**  \\n*Prepared : 2026‑04‑11*  \\n*Owner : QA Lead – [Your Name]*  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1.  Overview  \\n\\n| Item | Detail |\\n|------|--------|\\n| **Project / Epic** | KAN‑12 – *PRD – app.VWO.com* |\\n| **Product** | VWO Web‑Based Application (SaaS) – the primary UI for creating, managing and analysing A/B‑tests, personalization campaigns and feature‑flags. |\\n| **Target Audience** | Marketing & Product teams, analysts, developers (internal & external). |\\n| **Environment** | • Development (dev‑vwo.com) <br>• Staging (staging‑vwo.com) <br>• Production (app.vwo.com) <br>• Supported browsers: Chrome ≥ 106, Edge ≥ 106, Firefox ≥ 106, Safari ≥ 15 (desktop) and Chrome/ Safari on iOS/Android. |\\n| **Test Scope** | End‑to‑end functional verification, UI/UX validation, API contract testing, performance, security, accessibility, localisation and regression coverage for the core features of the VWO web app. |\\n| **Out‑of‑Scope** | • Third‑party integrations that are not part of the core product (e.g., CRM connectors) <br>• Mobile‑native SDKs (they have separate test suites) <br>• Data‑warehouse ETL pipelines (covered by data‑engineering). |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2.  Objectives  \\n\\n1. **Validate that all user‑flows defined in the PRD for app.VWO.com work as intended.**  \\n2. **Confirm UI consistency with design specifications (Figma/Sketch).**  \\n3. **Ensure API contracts (REST/GraphQL) are stable, correctly authenticated, and return expected data.**  \\n4. **Measure that critical pages load ≤ 2 seconds (first‑contentful‑paint) under typical load.**  \\n5. **Verify security hardening – OWASP Top‑10, role‑based access control, CSRF/XSS protection.**  \\n6. **Confirm accessibility compliance – WCAG 2.1 AA.**  \\n7. **Produce a reusable regression suite for every upcoming sprint.**  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3.  Test Items (Features)  \\n\\n| Feature | Description | Primary Owner |\\n|---------|-------------|---------------|\\n| **Dashboard** | Overview of active experiments, recent results, key metrics. | Product |\\n| **Experiment Builder** | Create A/B, multivariate, split‑URL, and feature‑flag experiments. | Product |\\n| **Targeting & Segmentation** | Audience definition (geo, device, custom attributes). | Product |\\n| **Variations Editor** | Visual editor (WYSIWYG) for UI changes, code editor for custom JS/CSS. | Design |\\n| **Goal & Metric Configuration** | Define primary/secondary goals, conversion events, custom JS goals. | Analytics |\\n| **Real‑time Reporting** | Live results, statistical significance, confidence intervals. | Analytics |\\n| **User Management & RBAC** | Invite users, assign roles (Admin, Analyst, Viewer). | Security |\\n| **Integrations** | Native connectors to Google Analytics, Segment, Adobe, etc. (core set). | Integration |\\n| **Notifications** | Email / Slack alerts for experiment status changes. | Ops |\\n| **Settings** | Account‑level config – time‑zone, currency, data retention. | Ops |\\n| **Help & Documentation** | In‑app tours, tooltips, searchable knowledge base. | Docs |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4.  Test Approach  \\n\\n| Type | Technique | Tools | Frequency |\\n|------|-----------|-------|-----------|\\n| **Functional / UI** | Manual exploratory + scripted UI tests | Selenium WebDriver (JavaScript/Playwright), Cypress, TestRail for test‑case management | Every sprint (smoke) + nightly regression |\\n| **API** | Contract testing, positive/negative flows | Postman/Newman, RestAssured, Pact (consumer‑driven) | CI pipeline on each PR |\\n| **Performance** | Load, stress & soak tests on key pages (Dashboard, Builder) | k6, JMeter, Lighthouse CI | Weekly + pre‑release |\\n| **Security** | Static analysis, dynamic scanning, penetration tests | Snyk, OWASP ZAP, Burp Suite, npm audit | Monthly; on major releases |\\n| **Accessibility** | Automated scans + manual keyboard/ screen‑reader checks | axe‑core (Cypress), Wave, NVDA/VoiceOver | Every release candidate |\\n| **Cross‑Browser / Device** | Matrix testing on real devices & emulators | BrowserStack, Sauce Labs | Every sprint |\\n| **Localization** | Verify UI strings for supported locales (en, fr, de, es, ja) | i18n‑test, custom locale scripts | Regression |\\n| **Usability** | Heuristic evaluation, user‑testing sessions | Lookback, Hotjar recordings | Early prototype & after major UI changes |\\n| **Data Integrity** | End‑to‑end flow validation – data captured in reporting matches actions performed | SQL queries, BigQuery validation scripts | Regression |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5.  Test Deliverables  \\n\\n| Deliverable | Format | Owner | Due |\\n|-------------|--------|-------|-----|\\n| **Test Strategy Document** | PDF/Confluence | QA Lead | 2026‑04‑15 |\\n| **Test Cases (Functional)** | TestRail test suite (≈ 250 cases) | QA Engineers | 2026‑04‑22 |\\n| **Automation Scripts** | Git repo (playwright‑tests/) | Automation Engineer | 2026‑04‑28 |\\n| **API Test Collections** | Postman workspace | API QA | 2026‑04‑20 |\\n| **Performance Test Results** | k6 reports, Grafana dashboards | Performance Engineer | 2026‑05‑01 |\\n| **Security Scan Report** | PDF (OWASP ZAP) | Security Engineer | 2026‑05‑03 |\\n| **Accessibility Report** | axe‑core JSON + summary | Accessibility Lead | 2026‑05‑03 |\\n| **Test Summary Report** | Confluence page + PDF | QA Lead | 2026‑05‑05 |\\n| **Defect Log** | JIRA (Bug) | QA Team | Ongoing |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 6.  Test Schedule (High‑Level)\\n\\n| Milestone | Date | Activity |\\n|-----------|------|----------|\\n| **Kick‑off / Requirement Review** | 2026‑04‑12 | Review PRD, design assets, acceptance criteria |\\n| **Test Case Authoring** | 2026‑04‑13 → 2026‑04‑20 | Write functional & non‑functional test cases |\\n| **Automation Sprint 1** | 2026‑04‑14 → 2026‑04‑28 | Core flows (login, dashboard, experiment creation) |\\n| **Smoke Build Validation** | 2026‑04‑22 | Run smoke suite on CI |\\n| **Performance Baseline** | 2026‑04‑24 | Run k6 load tests (100‑500 concurrent users) |\\n| **Security Scan** | 2026‑04‑27 | OWASP ZAP baseline |\\n| **Accessibility Scan** | 2026‑04‑28 | axe‑core CI integration |\\n| **Regression Run (Nightly)** | 2026‑04‑29 → 2026‑05‑04 | Full suite on staging |\\n| **UAT Sign‑off** | 2026‑05‑04 | Business stakeholders review |\\n| **Production Release** | 2026‑05‑05 | Deploy to app.vwo.com |\\n| **Post‑Release Smoke** | 2026‑05‑06 | Verify critical paths in prod |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 7.  Resources  \\n\\n| Role | Count | Responsibilities |\\n|------|-------|------------------|\\n| QA Lead | 1 | Test plan governance, risk management |\\n| QA Engineers (Functional) | 3 | Test case design, manual execution, defect triage |\\n| Automation Engineer | 2 | Script development, CI integration |\\n| API QA Engineer | 1 | API contract tests, mock services |\\n| Performance Engineer | 1 | Load & stress test design |\\n| Security Engineer | 1 | Vulnerability scanning, pen‑test coordination |\\n| Accessibility Lead | 1 | WCAG compliance verification |\\n| DevOps / CI Engineer | 1 | Pipeline setup for automated tests |\\n| Product Owner / Business Analyst | 1 | Clarify acceptance criteria, sign‑off |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 8.  Entry & Exit Criteria  \\n\\n### Entry Criteria  \\n\\n* PRD and UI mock‑ups are approved and available in Confluence/Figma.  \\n* Development branch is **feature‑complete** (no “TODO” tags).  \\n* Test environment (staging‑vwo.com) is provisioned with latest code and test data.  \\n* All required test data (users, experiments, goals) is seeded.  \\n\\n### Exit Criteria  \\n\\n* **All** test cases in the *Critical* and *High* severity buckets have passed.  \\n* No *Critical* defects remain open; *High* defects are either fixed or have an agreed‑upon mitigation.  \\n* Performance benchmarks met: <2 s FCP for Dashboard, <3 s for Experiment Builder under 200 concurrent users.  \\n* Security scan reports show **0** OWASP Top‑10 *Critical* findings.  \\n* Accessibility score ≥ 90 % (WCAG AA).  \\n* Regression suite executed on the release candidate with ≤ 1 % failure rate (excluding known flaky tests).  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## 9.  Risks & Mitigations  \\n\\n| Risk | Impact | Probability | Mitigation |\\n|------|--------|-------------|------------|\\n| **Incomplete requirements** (PRD missing edge‑cases) | Gaps in test coverage | Medium | Conduct early walkthrough with PO; add exploratory testing charter. |\\n| **Flaky UI automation** (dynamic IDs, async loads) | Delayed pipeline, false failures | High | Use robust selectors (data‑test‑id), add explicit waits, implement retry logic. |\\n| **Third‑party API rate limits** during integration tests | Test failures, blocked CI | Low | Use mock servers (WireMock) for CI; schedule real‑API calls off‑peak. |\\n| **Performance bottleneck on staging** (limited infra) | Inaccurate load test results | Medium | Use dedicated performance testing environment or cloud‑based load generators. |\\n| **Security scan false positives** | Wasted effort, delayed release | Low | Triage findings with security team; whitelist known safe patterns. |\\n| **Cross‑browser incompatibilities** (Safari on iOS) | UI breakage for end users | Medium | Add dedicated iOS Safari matrix in BrowserStack; early UI testing. |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 10.  Assumptions  \\n\\n* All design assets (Figma) are final and reflect the production UI.  \\n* Test data generation scripts are available and can create experiments, users, and goals on demand.  \\n* The CI/CD pipeline can be modified to include automated test stages without affecting release cadence.  \\n* The security team will allocate a 2‑day window for a focused penetration test before production go‑live.  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## 11.  Sample Test Cases (excerpt)  \\n\\n| TC‑ID | Title | Description | Pre‑conditions | Steps | Expected Result | Severity |\\n|-------|-------|-------------|----------------|-------|-----------------|----------|\\n| **TC‑F001** | Login – Valid Credentials | Verify that a registered user can log in. | User exists, password set. | 1. Navigate to `https://app.vwo.com` <br>2. Enter email & password <br>3. Click **Sign In** | Dashboard loads, user avatar displayed, session token set. | Critical |\\n| **TC‑F002** | Login – Invalid Password | Ensure proper error handling for wrong password. | User exists. | Same as above but with wrong password. | Inline error “Invalid email or password” shown, no navigation. | High |\\n| **TC‑F003** | Create New A/B Experiment (Visual Builder) | End‑to‑end creation of an A/B test using the visual editor. | User logged in, at least one website added. | 1. Click **Create Experiment** <br>2. Choose *A/B Test* <br>3. Select website <br>4. Use visual editor to create Variation‑B <br>5. Set Goal (e.g., Click‑through) <br>6. Save & Activate | Experiment appears in Dashboard with *Running* status; variation preview works; goal tracking pixel injected. | Critical |\\n| **TC‑F004** | Audience Targeting – Geo Filter | Verify that an experiment only serves to users in the selected country. | Experiment active with geo filter set to “United States”. | 1. Simulate request from US IP (using VPN) <br>2. Load target page <br>3. Observe variation displayed. <br>4. Simulate request from India IP. | US IP sees Variation‑B, India IP sees Control. | High |\\n| **TC‑API001** | GET `/api/v1/experiments` – Authenticated | Validate API returns list of experiments for the logged‑in user. | Bearer token obtained via login API. | Send GET request with Authorization header. | HTTP 200, JSON schema matches contract, only experiments belonging to the account are returned. | Critical |\\n| **TC‑PERF001** | Dashboard Load – 200 concurrent users | Measure response time under load. | Staging environment, k6 script ready. | Run k6 with 200 VUs for 5 min. | 95 % of requests ≤\",\"generationInfo\":{\"finish_reason\":\"length\"}}]]},\"tokenUsage\":{\"completionTokens\":3072,\"promptTokens\":1980,\"totalTokens\":5052}}}"}}
